N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 18 ยง 320.5 - Withdrawal of approval or other changes

State Regulations

Nothing in this Part shall limit the right of the
department for good reason and upon appropriate notice: (a) to withdraw approval of a local
equivalent of a required form supplied by the department; (b) to amend its basic minimum requirements
on required forms not supplied by the department; (c) to change the status of a required form
as between those supplied by the department and those which are not; or
(d) to change the status of
forms as between recommended and required. Notes
